You gotta come in here
and call the hospital!

265
00:39:26,460 --> 00:39:28,378
Come on, man! I'm serious about this!

266
00:39:28,462 --> 00:39:31,006
I can't do everything by myself, man!

267
00:39:31,090 --> 00:39:33,842
No! Let go!

268
00:39:33,926 --> 00:39:37,596
No! No!

269
00:39:41,225 --> 00:39:43,518
Oh! No!

270
00:39:43,603 --> 00:39:46,104
No! No! No!

271
00:39:50,860 --> 00:39:52,277
Hey, man.

272
00:40:25,561 --> 00:40:27,145
Um –

273
00:40:34,779 --> 00:40:36,696
Aw, man.

274
00:40:52,505 --> 00:40:55,423
Okay, Aunt Ruth, I'll try.

275
00:40:55,508 --> 00:41:00,720
I'm gonna study those lines
until I know 'em inside out.

276
00:41:00,805 --> 00:41:03,932
Yep, either right here on
this fabulous leather couch...

277
00:41:04,016 --> 00:41:05,934
or I'll take them with a coffee
into the courtyard...

278
00:41:06,018 --> 00:41:08,770
like a regular movie star.

279
00:41:08,854 --> 00:41:11,356
Oh, I got a real shock
to find your friend Rita here.

280
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:14,651
She was in the shower,
and I opened the door.

281
00:41:14,735 --> 00:41:16,319
Rita.

282
00:41:17,321 --> 00:41:19,030
What do you mean?

283
00:41:20,116 --> 00:41:23,285
Well, she was in an accident.

284
00:41:23,369 --> 00:41:26,079
Rita, your friend.

285
00:41:27,707 --> 00:41:30,041
No, Coco unlocked the door.

286
00:41:31,502 --> 00:41:33,044
No, she didn't see her.

287
00:41:34,839 --> 00:41:36,798
She's sleeping.

288
00:41:37,967 --> 00:41:42,178
I'm sure there's some explanation for this.
I don't think we have to do that.

289
00:41:44,640 --> 00:41:48,643
Please don't worry.
Aunt Ruth, we don't need the police.

290
00:42:01,449 --> 00:42:03,408
You're awake.

291
00:42:07,955 --> 00:42:09,873
I think I misunderstood.

292
00:42:09,957 --> 00:42:13,501
I thought you knew my aunt,
and that's why you were here.

293
00:42:13,586 --> 00:42:17,255
I just talked to my aunt on the phone,
and she wants me to call the police.

294
00:42:23,304 --> 00:42:25,680
Rita?

295
00:42:28,934 --> 00:42:31,436
I'm sorry. I –

296
00:42:31,520 --> 00:42:33,438
What is it, Rita?

297
00:42:37,234 --> 00:42:39,444
I thought when I woke up –

298
00:42:39,528 --> 00:42:42,030
I thought sleep would do it.

299
00:42:42,114 --> 00:42:44,032
What's wrong?

300
00:42:46,786 --> 00:42:49,204
I don't know who I am.

301
00:42:49,288 --> 00:42:51,373
What do you mean? You're Rita.

302
00:42:51,457 --> 00:42:55,710
No, I'm not. I don't know what my name is.

303
00:42:55,795 --> 00:42:58,755
I don't know who I am.

304
00:43:08,474 --> 00:43:10,392
This is your purse.

305
00:43:10,476 --> 00:43:12,977
Your name must be in your purse.

306
00:43:14,730 --> 00:43:17,232
You want to know, don't you?

307
00:43:18,317 --> 00:43:20,485
- Yes, but –
- Open it.

308
00:44:55,581 --> 00:44:59,417
- So you don't want anything?
- Not here. No, thanks.

309
00:44:59,502 --> 00:45:04,047
- A drink or something?
- No. Thanks, though.

310
00:45:04,131 --> 00:45:06,841
I'll take a cigarette, if you have one.

311
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:12,347
Yeah, just reach inside
my shirt pocket there.

312
00:45:17,269 --> 00:45:19,479
Any new girls on the street lately?

313
00:45:21,941 --> 00:45:23,858
No.

314
00:45:23,943 --> 00:45:25,902
I haven't seen any.

315
00:45:27,571 --> 00:45:29,531
A brunette?

316
00:45:29,615 --> 00:45:31,574
Maybe a little beat-up?

317
00:45:32,660 --> 00:45:34,619
No.

318
00:45:38,165 --> 00:45:40,708
You keep your eyes open
for me, won't you, baby?

319
00:45:40,793 --> 00:45:44,045
- Sure.
- Yeah, you bet you will.

320
00:45:47,049 --> 00:45:48,967
That money –

321
00:45:50,844 --> 00:45:52,762
you don't know where it came from?

322
00:45:52,846 --> 00:45:54,639
Uh-uh.

323
00:45:56,684 --> 00:46:01,020
When you think of them –
the money and the key –

324
00:46:02,982 --> 00:46:05,942
does it make you remember anything?

325
00:46:07,820 --> 00:46:10,363
There's something –

326
00:46:11,824 --> 00:46:14,576
something... there, I –

327
00:46:26,839 --> 00:46:28,548
What did you say?

328
00:46:28,632 --> 00:46:30,758
They fired everyone.

329
00:46:30,843 --> 00:46:33,094
Who fired everyone?

330
00:46:33,178 --> 00:46:37,432
Ray did – Wait!
I-I'm talking on the phone.

331
00:46:37,516 --> 00:46:40,602
And then they closed the set.
Everybody's gone.

332
00:46:40,686 --> 00:46:43,730
You'd better get down here, Adam.

333
00:46:43,814 --> 00:46:45,398
No.

334
00:46:45,482 --> 00:46:48,234
You've gotta talk to Ray.
You've gotta fix this.

335
00:46:48,319 --> 00:46:51,446
- I'm going home.
- Home?

336
00:46:51,530 --> 00:46:53,489
Meet me at the office.
We've gotta do something.

337
00:46:53,574 --> 00:46:55,491
You've gotta do something, Adam.

338
00:46:55,576 --> 00:46:57,619
I'm going home, Cynthia.

339
00:46:57,703 --> 00:46:59,746
Adam, listen to me. This isn't like you.

340
00:46:59,830 --> 00:47:01,748
Please come to the office.

341
00:47:01,832 --> 00:47:04,125
- There's gotta be something we can do.
- I'm going home.

342
00:47:15,220 --> 00:47:17,555
I wonder where you were going.

343
00:47:22,394 --> 00:47:24,562
Mulholland Drive.

344
00:47:29,485 --> 00:47:31,402
Mulholland Drive?

345
00:47:33,697 --> 00:47:35,823
That's where I was going –

346
00:47:35,908 --> 00:47:39,035
Mulholland Drive.

347
00:47:40,204 --> 00:47:42,830
Maybe that's where the accident was.

348
00:47:44,124 --> 00:47:46,959
There must be a police report.
We could call.

349
00:47:47,044 --> 00:47:48,503
No.

350
00:47:48,587 --> 00:47:53,007
We could call anonymously from a pay phone
just to see if there was an accident.

351
00:47:53,092 --> 00:47:55,551
Come on.
It'll be just like in the movies.

352
00:47:55,636 --> 00:47:58,221
We'll pretend to be someone else.

353
00:47:59,932 --> 00:48:01,933
I wanna walk around anyway.

354
00:48:02,017 --> 00:48:05,395
I'm in Hollywood,
and I haven't even seen any of it.

355
00:48:05,479 --> 00:48:08,439
Come on, Rita. Do you feel up to it?

356
00:48:15,739 --> 00:48:17,657
Okay.

357
00:48:17,741 --> 00:48:19,992
But... just –

358
00:48:21,995 --> 00:48:24,455
just to see.

359
00:48:24,540 --> 00:48:28,710
Just to see if there was an accident...

360
00:48:28,794 --> 00:48:31,295
on Mulholland Drive.

361
00:49:13,839 --> 00:49:15,339
Lorraine?

362
00:49:16,884 --> 00:49:18,843
Lorraine, you home?

363
00:49:22,222 --> 00:49:23,806
Lorraine?

364
00:49:44,203 --> 00:49:46,120
Now you've done it.

365
00:49:48,373 --> 00:49:51,709
Just forget you ever saw it.
It's better that way.

366
00:49:54,463 --> 00:49:57,548
What the hell are you even doing here?

367
00:50:09,394 --> 00:50:11,062
What are you doing?

368
00:50:14,983 --> 00:50:16,400
That's my jewelry!

369
00:50:33,794 --> 00:50:37,171
That bastard! You bastard!

370
00:50:37,256 --> 00:50:39,423
He's probably upset, Lorraine.

371
00:50:45,722 --> 00:50:47,098
What are you doing?

372
00:50:49,476 --> 00:50:52,728
Stop it! Stop it!

373
00:50:52,813 --> 00:50:55,022
Adam, stop it!

374
00:50:55,899 --> 00:50:58,359
Stop it! Stop it!

375
00:50:58,443 --> 00:51:02,864
Adam! Cut – Cut it out! Ow!

376
00:51:02,948 --> 00:51:06,242
You're hurting me! Gene!

377
00:51:06,326 --> 00:51:08,077
You're hurting me!

378
00:51:11,206 --> 00:51:14,876
That ain't no way to treat your wife, buddy.
I don't care what she's done.

379
00:51:16,295 --> 00:51:17,753
Throw him out!

380
00:51:18,547 --> 00:51:20,715
Throw him out!

381
00:51:20,799 --> 00:51:22,717
Damn you, Adam!

382
00:51:23,635 --> 00:51:25,094
Throw him out!

383
00:51:31,810 --> 00:51:33,895
Get out!

384
00:52:13,226 --> 00:52:14,810
Let's hide it.

385
00:53:00,440 --> 00:53:02,024
There's one.

386
00:53:17,958 --> 00:53:20,835
Hollywood Police Department.

387
00:53:20,919 --> 00:53:23,921
I'm inquiring about an accident that happened
last night on Mulholland Drive.

388
00:53:24,006 --> 00:53:26,424
Hold, please. I'll connect you to Traffic.

389
00:53:28,427 --> 00:53:31,929
- Sergeant Baxter.
- Hi. I'm inquiring –

390
00:53:33,598 --> 00:53:37,268
Well, I heard a sound last night that
sounded sort of like a car crash...

391
00:53:37,352 --> 00:53:41,355
and, well, I want to know if there was
an accident on Mulholland Drive.

392
00:53:41,440 --> 00:53:43,357
Yes, there was.

393
00:53:43,442 --> 00:53:46,527
- Can you tell me what happened?
- No, I can't.

394
00:53:46,611 --> 00:53:49,405
- Was anyone hurt?
- May I have your name, please?

395
00:53:56,329 --> 00:53:58,539
There was an accident.

396
00:53:58,623 --> 00:54:02,793
He wouldn't tell me anything else,
but that was your accident. I just know it was.

397
00:54:04,171 --> 00:54:06,756
Maybe there's something
about it in the papers.

398
00:54:06,840 --> 00:54:09,091
I'll buy you a cup of coffee
and we can see.

399
00:54:13,305 --> 00:54:16,599
Maybe it happened so late,
it's not in today's paper.

400
00:54:16,683 --> 00:54:18,642
There's nothing?

401
00:54:20,187 --> 00:54:22,980
Not that I can see.

402
00:54:24,149 --> 00:54:25,941
That's okay.

403
00:54:29,571 --> 00:54:31,489
Thanks...

404
00:54:33,658 --> 00:54:34,825
Diane.

405
00:54:40,582 --> 00:54:43,084
Will that be all?
Would you like your check?

406
00:54:43,168 --> 00:54:45,002
Rita, you want something?

407
00:54:47,964 --> 00:54:50,925
No, just – just the coffee.

408
00:54:51,009 --> 00:54:53,469
- We'll take our check.
- Okay.

409
00:54:59,518 --> 00:55:02,061
- What is it, Rita?
- Shh.

410
00:55:09,653 --> 00:55:12,113
I remember something.

411
00:55:12,197 --> 00:55:14,448
I remember something!

412
00:55:17,369 --> 00:55:20,788
- What is it?
- Diane Selwyn.

413
00:55:20,872 --> 00:55:23,374
Maybe that's my name!

414
00:55:24,835 --> 00:55:26,710
Selwyn. Selwyn.

415
00:55:28,713 --> 00:55:32,758
"D. Selwyn." It's the only one.

416
00:55:32,843 --> 00:55:34,802
I'm gonna call.

417
00:55:42,060 --> 00:55:44,353
It's strange to be calling yourself.

418
00:55:44,437 --> 00:55:47,106
Maybe it's not me.

419
00:55:55,240 --> 00:55:58,784
Hello, it's me. Leave a message.

420
00:56:01,371 --> 00:56:03,831
That's not my voice.

421
00:56:04,875 --> 00:56:06,834
But I know her.

422
00:56:08,753 --> 00:56:12,256
Maybe that isn't Diane Selwyn's voice.

423
00:56:12,340 --> 00:56:14,550
Maybe that's your roommate.

424
00:56:14,634 --> 00:56:17,011
Or if it is Diane Selwyn...

425
00:56:17,095 --> 00:56:20,306
she could tell you who you are.

426
00:56:20,390 --> 00:56:22,766
Maybe.

427
00:56:22,851 --> 00:56:24,935
Maybe. Maybe.

428
00:56:29,107 --> 00:56:32,193
♪ Baby ♪

429
00:56:37,782 --> 00:56:41,410
♪ Baby ♪

430
00:56:46,124 --> 00:56:50,377
♪ I'm gonna bring it on home to you ♪

431
00:56:50,462 --> 00:56:52,880
♪ I done bought my ticket ♪

432
00:56:52,964 --> 00:56:55,883
♪ I got my load ♪♪

433
00:56:57,802 --> 00:57:00,971
♪♪ Adam Kesher?

434
00:57:04,309 --> 00:57:06,435
- Adam Kesher!
- Yeah, right. Get lost!

435
00:57:06,519 --> 00:57:09,939
- This is Adam Kesher's house.
- Like hell it is. Get out! Now!

436
00:57:10,023 --> 00:57:12,775
Get out!

437
00:57:12,859 --> 00:57:15,236
Adam Kesher?

438
00:57:20,242 --> 00:57:23,953
Get out of here!
He's never coming back, ever!

439
00:57:25,997 --> 00:57:29,124
I guess you don't understand English.
She said leave!

440
00:57:29,209 --> 00:57:32,127
- Here's the door!
- Gene!

441
00:57:32,212 --> 00:57:34,838
Get out! Gene! Get out –

442
00:57:40,053 --> 00:57:42,012
Adam Kesher?

443
00:58:04,744 --> 00:58:06,537
Yeah, what is it, Cookie?

444
00:58:06,621 --> 00:58:11,709
I'm sorry, Mr. Kesher, but there seems to be
some problem with your credit cards.

445
00:58:11,793 --> 00:58:14,545
What? I-I pay you cash, Cookie.

446
00:58:16,715 --> 00:58:20,718
Mira, ese.
Two guys from your bank came by.

447
00:58:21,386 --> 00:58:23,053
My bank?

448
00:58:24,097 --> 00:58:26,849
- How-How'd they know I was here?
- I don't know.

449
00:58:27,892 --> 00:58:29,810
What'd they say?

450
00:58:29,894 --> 00:58:34,315
I'm afraid they said to tell you that
you're maxed out at your bank...

451
00:58:34,399 --> 00:58:37,735
and that your line of credit
has been canceled.

452
00:58:39,404 --> 00:58:42,990
That's unbelievable. Huh.

453
00:58:43,074 --> 00:58:45,284
Well, look, uh...

454
00:58:46,453 --> 00:58:49,371
I , uh – I don't know what's going on.

455
00:58:50,373 --> 00:58:53,083
That is so much baloney.

456
00:58:53,168 --> 00:58:54,710
Uh –

457
00:58:54,794 --> 00:58:57,004
But I got enough cash for you, Cookie.

458
00:58:57,088 --> 00:59:01,383
Oh, I know. I know. Don't worry.

459
00:59:01,468 --> 00:59:04,261
But, ese, I'm sorry.

460
00:59:04,346 --> 00:59:06,513
It was my duty to inform you.

461
00:59:07,849 --> 00:59:10,184
Oye, carnal.

462
00:59:10,268 --> 00:59:14,438
Whoever you're hiding from,
they know where you are.

463
00:59:16,274 --> 00:59:17,941
Right.

464
00:59:18,985 --> 00:59:20,652
I'm sorry.

465
00:59:43,301 --> 00:59:45,886
Hello?

466
00:59:45,970 --> 00:59:47,888
Someone maybe shut off my money.

467
00:59:47,972 --> 00:59:49,890
I know. Where are you, Adam?

468
00:59:49,974 --> 00:59:52,226
I'm sorry.
What do you mean, you know?

469
00:59:52,310 --> 00:59:56,605
Somebody called. When they couldn't get you,
they told me you were as good as broke.

470
00:59:56,689 --> 00:59:58,899
I didn't believe them,
so I made a few calls.

471
00:59:58,983 --> 01:00:01,318
- And?
- You're broke.

472
01:00:01,403 --> 01:00:02,945
Yeah, but I'm not broke!

473
01:00:03,029 --> 01:00:05,823
I know, but you're broke. Where are you?

474
01:00:07,283 --> 01:00:09,993
I'm at Cookie's, downtown.

475
01:00:10,078 --> 01:00:13,789
Do you know somebody
called the Cowboy?

476
01:00:14,749 --> 01:00:17,084
- The Cowboy?
- Yeah.

477
01:00:17,168 --> 01:00:18,460
The Cowboy.

478
01:00:18,545 --> 01:00:21,922
This guy, the Cowboy,
wants to see you.

479
01:00:22,006 --> 01:00:24,842
Jason said he thought it'd be a good idea.

480
01:00:26,052 --> 01:00:29,388
Oh, Jason thought it'd be a good idea
for me to go see the Cowboy.

481
01:00:29,472 --> 01:00:32,766
Well, should I wear my 10-gallon hat
and my six-shooters?

482
01:00:32,851 --> 01:00:36,437
Listen, something tells me that this guy
is connected to what's happening.

483
01:00:37,480 --> 01:00:41,442
Adam, I think you should do it,
and I think you should do it right away.

484
01:00:41,526 --> 01:00:43,444
What's going on, Cynthia?

485
01:00:43,528 --> 01:00:45,904
It's been a very strange day.

486
01:00:47,782 --> 01:00:49,700
And getting stranger.

487
01:00:52,078 --> 01:00:55,372
So, where do I meet this Cowboy?
Do I have to ride out to the range?

488
01:00:56,249 --> 01:00:58,459
Sort of, funny boy.

489
01:00:58,543 --> 01:01:00,544
If I tell him the meeting's on...

490
01:01:00,628 --> 01:01:03,464
you'll have to go to the top
of Beachwood Canyon...

491
01:01:03,548 --> 01:01:07,509
and there's a corral up there
where he'll be.

492
01:01:07,594 --> 01:01:10,179
Oh, you've gotta be kidding me.

493
01:01:10,263 --> 01:01:12,639
Will you meet with him?

494
01:01:12,724 --> 01:01:15,100
Yeah. Sure.

495
01:01:15,185 --> 01:01:18,312
No, i-it's been that kind of a day.
When?

496
01:01:18,396 --> 01:01:20,481
Um, I'll call him right away...

497
01:01:20,565 --> 01:01:23,233
and then I'll call you back.

498
01:01:23,318 --> 01:01:27,404
You know, you – you could stay
at my place if you – if you wanted.

499
01:01:27,489 --> 01:01:30,657
Uh, Cynthia, no.
I don't think that would be a good idea.

500
01:01:30,742 --> 01:01:32,993
I was just offering a place to stay.

501
01:01:33,077 --> 01:01:36,246
Yes, and I appreciate the offer, Cynthia.
I'll find a place.

502
01:01:36,331 --> 01:01:39,708
Just go and give that Cowboy a yodel
and get on back to me.

503
01:01:39,792 --> 01:01:42,711
Okay. But you don't know
what you're missing.

504
01:01:42,795 --> 01:01:46,840
Uh, just get along, little doggie,
and call me back.

505
01:01:58,770 --> 01:02:01,188
It's right about here – Sierra Bonita.

506
01:02:01,272 --> 01:02:03,190
Not too far away.

507
01:02:04,317 --> 01:02:06,276
What's wrong with that?

508
01:02:07,403 --> 01:02:09,321
I'm not sure about this.

509
01:02:11,199 --> 01:02:13,408
I know you're afraid of something.

510
01:02:14,786 --> 01:02:16,954
We'll be careful, I promise.

511
01:02:18,456 --> 01:02:22,084
Tomorrow, we'll go over there...

512
01:02:22,168 --> 01:02:24,253
and we'll find out.

513
01:02:37,475 --> 01:02:40,477
It'll be okay.

514
01:02:41,980 --> 01:02:43,897
It's probably Coco.

515
01:02:47,860 --> 01:02:50,153
Yes? May I help you?

516
01:02:50,238 --> 01:02:52,447
Someone is in trouble.

517
01:02:54,284 --> 01:02:57,077
Who are you?

518
01:02:57,161 --> 01:02:59,997
What are you doing in Ruth's apartment?

519
01:03:00,081 --> 01:03:02,165
She's letting me stay here.

520
01:03:02,250 --> 01:03:04,835
I'm her niece. My name's Betty.

521
01:03:04,919 --> 01:03:06,837
No, it's not.

522
01:03:06,921 --> 01:03:09,298
That's not what she said.

523
01:03:09,382 --> 01:03:14,094
Someone is in trouble!
Something bad is happening!

524
01:03:14,178 --> 01:03:17,639
Well, I-I'm sorry,
but I don't know who you are, and –

525
01:03:17,724 --> 01:03:20,767
Louise? What are you doing, Louise?

526
01:03:20,852 --> 01:03:22,936
I – Oh, Coco.

527
01:03:23,021 --> 01:03:26,565
I've been trying to get a hold of you
since 3:00 this afternoon.

528
01:03:26,649 --> 01:03:30,152
That one is in my room,
and she won't leave.

529
01:03:30,236 --> 01:03:33,280
I want you to get her out.
I want you to get her out now!

530
01:03:33,364 --> 01:03:36,700
Uh, this is Louise Bonner.
I'm sure she meant well.

531
01:03:36,784 --> 01:03:40,871
Louise, this is Betty.
This is Ruth's niece.

532
01:03:40,955 --> 01:03:43,999
In fact, fortunately I was just on my way
over here to see Betty.

533
01:03:44,083 --> 01:03:46,793
Betty's a young actress,
and I was just delivering...

534
01:03:46,878 --> 01:03:50,213
some faxed pages of a scene
for a big audition tomorrow.

535
01:03:50,298 --> 01:03:53,050
- Well, here they are, honey.
- Oh, thank you.

536
01:03:53,134 --> 01:03:55,719
Come along now, Louise.
I'll take you home.

537
01:03:55,803 --> 01:03:57,471
I'm sorry.
It happens sometimes.

538
01:03:57,555 --> 01:03:58,805
- No.
- Come on.

539
01:03:58,890 --> 01:04:01,308
No. She said it was someone else
who was in trouble.

540
01:04:01,392 --> 01:04:03,226
Stop it, Louise. I'm taking you home.

541
01:04:04,562 --> 01:04:06,521
Come on. I-I –

542
01:04:06,606 --> 01:04:08,565
- Good night, Betty.
- Good night.

543
01:04:09,442 --> 01:04:11,401
Good night.

544
01:04:21,579 --> 01:04:23,580
Whoa.

545
01:04:49,273 --> 01:04:51,608
Cowboy.

546
01:05:59,844 --> 01:06:03,180
- Howdy.
- Howdy to you.

547
01:06:05,683 --> 01:06:07,017
Beautiful evenin'.

548
01:06:08,519 --> 01:06:09,978
Yeah.

549
01:06:11,397 --> 01:06:14,065
Sure wanna thank you for comin'
all the way up here to see me...

550
01:06:14,150 --> 01:06:17,319
from that nice hotel downtown.

551
01:06:18,821 --> 01:06:21,948
No problem. What's on your mind?

552
01:06:22,033 --> 01:06:26,495
Well, now, here's a man
who wants to get right down to it.

553
01:06:26,579 --> 01:06:29,372
Kinda anxious to get to it, are ya?

554
01:06:29,457 --> 01:06:31,041
Whatever.

555
01:06:32,877 --> 01:06:34,461
A man's attitude –

556
01:06:35,546 --> 01:06:38,340
A man's attitude goes some ways...

557
01:06:38,424 --> 01:06:41,259
to the way his life will be.

558
01:06:41,344 --> 01:06:43,804
Is that something you might agree with?

559
01:06:43,888 --> 01:06:45,639
Sure.

560
01:06:45,723 --> 01:06:47,641
Now, did you answer...

561
01:06:47,725 --> 01:06:50,352
because that's what you thought
I wanted to hear...

562
01:06:50,436 --> 01:06:52,646
or did you think about what I said...

563
01:06:52,730 --> 01:06:56,691
and answer 'cause
you truly believe that to be right?

564
01:06:57,944 --> 01:07:01,988
I agree with what you said. Truly.

565
01:07:03,741 --> 01:07:05,700
What'd I say?

566
01:07:08,538 --> 01:07:12,249
That a man's attitude determines,
to a large extent, how his life will be.

567
01:07:13,918 --> 01:07:16,503
So since you agree...

568
01:07:16,587 --> 01:07:21,550
you must be a person
who does not care about the good life.

569
01:07:21,634 --> 01:07:23,844
How's that?

570
01:07:25,429 --> 01:07:29,474
Well, stop for a little second
and think about it.

571
01:07:29,559 --> 01:07:31,768
Can you do that for me?

572
01:07:34,146 --> 01:07:37,232
Okay. I'm thinkin'.

573
01:07:40,653 --> 01:07:42,696
No, you're not thinkin'.

574
01:07:42,780 --> 01:07:45,782
You're too busy
bein' a smart aleck to be thinkin'.

575
01:07:47,118 --> 01:07:50,954
Now, I want you to think
and stop bein' a smart aleck.

576
01:07:51,038 --> 01:07:52,956
Can you try that for me?

577
01:07:53,875 --> 01:07:57,961
Look, where's this going?
What do you want me to do?

578
01:07:58,045 --> 01:08:01,339
There's sometimes a buggy.

579
01:08:01,424 --> 01:08:03,800
How many drivers does a buggy have?

580
01:08:03,885 --> 01:08:05,969
One.

581
01:08:06,053 --> 01:08:10,015
So let's just say
I'm drivin' this buggy...

582
01:08:10,099 --> 01:08:14,227
and if you fix your attitude,
you can ride along with me.

583
01:08:15,146 --> 01:08:16,563
Okay.

584
01:08:16,647 --> 01:08:19,566
I want you to go back to work tomorrow.

585
01:08:20,568 --> 01:08:23,111
You were recasting
the lead actress anyway.

586
01:08:23,195 --> 01:08:27,365
Audition many girls for the part.

587
01:08:27,450 --> 01:08:32,329
When you see the girl that was shown
to you earlier today, you will say...

588
01:08:32,413 --> 01:08:35,749
"This is the girl."

589
01:08:35,833 --> 01:08:38,293
The rest of the cast can stay.

590
01:08:38,377 --> 01:08:41,004
That's up to you.

591
01:08:41,088 --> 01:08:43,965
But that lead girl is not up to you.

592
01:08:46,010 --> 01:08:48,887
Now, you will see me one more time...

593
01:08:48,971 --> 01:08:51,514
if you do good.

594
01:08:51,599 --> 01:08:54,643
You'll see me two more times...

595
01:08:54,727 --> 01:08:57,103
if you do bad.

596
01:08:57,188 --> 01:08:59,147
Good night.

597
01:09:23,798 --> 01:09:25,715
You're still here?

598
01:09:25,800 --> 01:09:28,635
I came back. I thought
that's what you wanted.

599
01:09:28,719 --> 01:09:30,637
Nobody wants you here.

600
01:09:30,721 --> 01:09:33,348
Really?

601
01:09:33,432 --> 01:09:36,101
My parents are right upstairs.
They think you've left.

602
01:09:36,185 --> 01:09:40,313
- So? Surprise.
- I can call them. I can call my dad.

603
01:09:40,398 --> 01:09:42,565
But you won't.

604
01:09:42,650 --> 01:09:45,986
If you're trying to blackmail me,
it's not gonna work.

605
01:09:46,070 --> 01:09:48,029
You're playing a dangerous game here.

606
01:09:48,114 --> 01:09:50,490
You know what I want.
It's not that difficult.

607
01:09:50,574 --> 01:09:54,077
Get out! Get out before I call my dad!

608
01:09:54,161 --> 01:09:57,330
He trusts you. You're his best friend.

609
01:09:57,415 --> 01:09:59,833
This will be the end of everything.

610
01:09:59,917 --> 01:10:03,169
What about you?
What will your dad think about you?

611
01:10:03,254 --> 01:10:07,590
Stop! Just stop it!
That's what you said from the beginning!

612
01:10:07,675 --> 01:10:11,011
Now, if I tell what happened,
they'll arrest you and put you in jail.

613
01:10:11,095 --> 01:10:13,221
So, get out of here before –

614
01:10:14,265 --> 01:10:16,182
B-Before what?

615
01:10:16,267 --> 01:10:20,186
Before... I kill you.

616
01:10:20,271 --> 01:10:22,605
Then they'd put you in jail.

617
01:10:25,776 --> 01:10:29,696
Then I cry, cry, cry,
and then I say with big emotion...

618
01:10:29,780 --> 01:10:32,532
"I hate you! I hate us both!"

619
01:10:35,703 --> 01:10:39,539
- Such a lame scene.
- But you are really good.

620
01:10:40,791 --> 01:10:43,084
Thank you, darling.

621
01:10:57,933 --> 01:11:00,226
Hi there. Who are you?

622
01:11:01,645 --> 01:11:03,563
Uh –

623
01:11:03,647 --> 01:11:05,565
Betty?

624
01:11:11,363 --> 01:11:14,991
Uh, Betty,
can I see you outside for a minute?

625
01:11:29,507 --> 01:11:32,967
- What is it, Coco?
- Your aunt called.

626
01:11:34,512 --> 01:11:36,096
I was afraid of that.

627
01:11:36,180 --> 01:11:38,556
She wants to know
who's staying in her apartment.

628
01:11:40,059 --> 01:11:43,019
It's just for a night or two,
until she finds her own place.

629
01:11:43,104 --> 01:11:45,522
I tried to explain that to Aunt Ruth,
but the connection was bad...

630
01:11:45,606 --> 01:11:48,608
and her plane was leaving,
and she got it all mixed up.

631
01:11:48,692 --> 01:11:50,860
I kept telling her that
it was my friend Rita...

632
01:11:50,945 --> 01:11:53,363
and she kept saying
she didn't know any Ritas.

633
01:11:54,698 --> 01:11:56,783
- Look at me straight, sweetie.
- Coco.

634
01:11:56,867 --> 01:11:58,952
She's very nice.

635
01:11:59,036 --> 01:12:00,954
Honey, you're a good kid.

636
01:12:01,038 --> 01:12:04,165
But what you're telling me
is a load of horse puckey...

637
01:12:04,250 --> 01:12:07,085
even though it comes from a good place.

638
01:12:07,169 --> 01:12:09,712
Now, I'm gonna trust you
to sort this thing out.

639
01:12:09,797 --> 01:12:11,714
Thank you.

640
01:12:11,799 --> 01:12:14,134
Don't make me out to be a sucker.

641
01:12:14,218 --> 01:12:16,511
Louise Bonner said
there's trouble in there.

642
01:12:16,595 --> 01:12:18,513
Remember last night?

643
01:12:18,597 --> 01:12:22,142
Well, sometimes she's wrong.

644
01:12:22,226 --> 01:12:26,020
But if there is trouble, get rid of it.

645
01:12:36,240 --> 01:12:38,324
Is everything all right?

646
01:12:38,409 --> 01:12:40,326
Is it bad for you that I'm here?

647
01:12:40,411 --> 01:12:43,663
No, no. Everything is A-okay.

648
01:12:43,747 --> 01:12:45,957
Now, I've gotta fix that sandwich.

649
01:12:46,041 --> 01:12:48,960
And my audition is in one hour!

650
01:13:08,939 --> 01:13:11,733
I hope I'm back in a couple of hours.

651
01:13:11,817 --> 01:13:14,903
- And don't drink all the Coke.
- Good luck!

652
01:13:14,987 --> 01:13:18,239
Now, when I get back I'll keep
the cab waiting, so be ready to go.

653
01:13:18,324 --> 01:13:20,283
- Okay.
- Okay?

654
01:13:48,437 --> 01:13:50,313
Voilà.

655
01:13:50,397 --> 01:13:52,815
Betty Elms...

656
01:13:52,900 --> 01:13:56,486
I would like you to meet
Jack Tuptman, my assistant...

657
01:13:57,446 --> 01:13:59,322
Woody Katz...

658
01:13:59,406 --> 01:14:01,908
who we have cast in the part of Chuck
and will do the scene with you...

659
01:14:03,827 --> 01:14:05,453
Bob Brooker, our director...

660
01:14:05,537 --> 01:14:08,248
and Julie Chadwick.

661
01:14:08,332 --> 01:14:10,833
Now, our surprise guest...

662
01:14:10,918 --> 01:14:13,086
Linney James.

663
01:14:13,170 --> 01:14:15,588
Alas, we can't afford her
to cast our show...

664
01:14:15,673 --> 01:14:18,299
but, well, as casting agents go...

665
01:14:18,384 --> 01:14:20,843
she is the best.

666
01:14:20,928 --> 01:14:24,138
Why, thank you, Wally. Hello, Betty.

667
01:14:24,223 --> 01:14:26,099
Very pleased to meet you.

668
01:14:26,183 --> 01:14:28,434
This is my assistant, Nicki.

669
01:14:29,186 --> 01:14:32,105
Oh!
And the ever-lovely Martha.

670
01:14:32,189 --> 01:14:34,857
Martha Johnson, whom you met out front.

671
01:14:37,027 --> 01:14:38,987
Hi.

672
01:14:39,071 --> 01:14:42,073
So, shall we... give it a go?

673
01:14:43,450 --> 01:14:47,245
Uh, would you like a water
or a coffee before we begin?

674
01:14:47,329 --> 01:14:49,247
No, I'm-I'm fine.

675
01:14:49,331 --> 01:14:52,792
Well, then, let's everyone take a seat.

676
01:14:55,421 --> 01:14:56,796
Betty...

677
01:14:56,880 --> 01:15:00,508
why don't you join Woody over there
and we'll play the scene.

678
01:15:01,635 --> 01:15:05,054
Bob, do you have anything you wish to say?

679
01:15:05,139 --> 01:15:08,141
Something to Betty before we begin?

680
01:15:08,225 --> 01:15:10,893
No. It's not a contest.

681
01:15:12,396 --> 01:15:16,357
The two of them, with themselves.

682
01:15:18,235 --> 01:15:21,946
So don't play it for real...

683
01:15:22,031 --> 01:15:24,991
until it gets real.

684
01:15:29,913 --> 01:15:31,414
Okay.

685
01:15:32,249 --> 01:15:36,002
- Just tell me where it hurts, baby.
- What?

686
01:15:36,086 --> 01:15:38,254
Hey, Bobby,
I wanna play this one nice and close...

687
01:15:38,339 --> 01:15:40,173
like we did with that other girl –

688
01:15:40,257 --> 01:15:43,009
What's her name? The one with
the black hair. It felt kind of good.

689
01:15:43,093 --> 01:15:45,011
- What do you think?
- That's good, Woody.

690
01:15:45,095 --> 01:15:47,347
Just don't rush that line again.

691
01:15:47,431 --> 01:15:51,017
I told you, the line
where you say, "Before what?"

692
01:15:52,102 --> 01:15:54,812
Bobby, acting is reacting.

693
01:15:54,897 --> 01:15:58,316
I just play off 'em. They all say, um...

694
01:15:58,400 --> 01:16:00,318
"They're gonna arrest you," like that.

695
01:16:00,402 --> 01:16:02,695
Then, "They'll put you in jail."
They all say it the same way.

696
01:16:02,780 --> 01:16:04,989
So when they say it, I just react.

697
01:16:05,074 --> 01:16:06,532
- What's your name?
- Betty.

698
01:16:06,617 --> 01:16:11,996
Yeah, Betty.
Look, you don't rush it, I don't rush it. Okay?

699
01:16:12,081 --> 01:16:14,999
Now, we're gonna play this
nice and close.

700
01:16:15,084 --> 01:16:17,960
Just like in the movies, okay?

701
01:16:20,464 --> 01:16:22,715
Dad's best friend goes to work.

702
01:16:24,009 --> 01:16:26,135
Bob?

703
01:16:28,514 --> 01:16:31,474
And... action!

704
01:16:36,563 --> 01:16:38,481
You're still here.

705
01:16:39,817 --> 01:16:43,569
I came back.
Thought that's what you wanted.

706
01:16:43,654 --> 01:16:46,906
- Nobody wants you here.
- Really?

707
01:16:46,990 --> 01:16:49,617
My parents are right upstairs.

708
01:16:49,701 --> 01:16:51,619
They think you've left.

709
01:16:51,703 --> 01:16:53,663
So, surprise!

710
01:16:53,747 --> 01:16:57,083
I can call them. I can call my dad.

711
01:16:57,167 --> 01:16:59,127
But you won't.

712
01:17:14,810 --> 01:17:17,353
You're playing a dangerous game here.

713
01:17:19,106 --> 01:17:21,983
If you're trying to blackmail me...

714
01:17:22,067 --> 01:17:24,193
it's not gonna work.

715
01:17:26,113 --> 01:17:28,531
You know what I want.

716
01:17:28,615 --> 01:17:30,533
It's not that difficult.

717
01:17:33,579 --> 01:17:35,538
Get out.

718
01:17:37,249 --> 01:17:40,626
Get out before I call my dad.

719
01:17:40,711 --> 01:17:42,962
He trusts you.

720
01:17:43,046 --> 01:17:45,214
You're his...

721
01:17:45,299 --> 01:17:47,425
best friend.

722
01:17:51,180 --> 01:17:53,598
This will be the end of everything.

723
01:17:56,226 --> 01:17:57,894
What about you?

724
01:17:57,978 --> 01:18:00,313
What'll your dad think about you?

725
01:18:00,397 --> 01:18:01,939
Don't.

726
01:18:03,192 --> 01:18:05,109
Stop it.

727
01:18:06,653 --> 01:18:08,821
That's what you said from the beginning.

728
01:18:10,908 --> 01:18:12,825
If I tell them what happened...

729
01:18:12,910 --> 01:18:15,536
they'll arrest you and put you in jail.

730
01:18:22,544 --> 01:18:24,670
So get out of here...

731
01:18:24,755 --> 01:18:26,714
before –

732
01:18:29,843 --> 01:18:31,761
Before what?

733
01:18:50,113 --> 01:18:52,698
Before...

734
01:18:52,783 --> 01:18:54,784
I kill you.

735
01:19:10,050 --> 01:19:12,552
Well, then they'd put you in jail.

736
01:19:21,228 --> 01:19:22,937
I hate you.

737
01:19:24,856 --> 01:19:26,816
I hate us both.

738
01:19:42,499 --> 01:19:45,585
- I'm gonna take her over there.
- Yeah, big time.

739
01:19:49,798 --> 01:19:51,716
Well, there it was.

740
01:19:51,800 --> 01:19:55,094
Yeah, there it was, all right.

741
01:19:55,178 --> 01:19:57,972
Baby, you've got a way with you. Really.

742
01:19:58,056 --> 01:19:59,807
Bob?

743
01:20:01,685 --> 01:20:04,562
Very good. Really.

744
01:20:04,646 --> 01:20:07,273
I mean, it was forced, maybe...

745
01:20:07,357 --> 01:20:11,360
but still humanistic.

746
01:20:11,445 --> 01:20:14,113
Yeah. Very good.

747
01:20:14,197 --> 01:20:17,033
Really. Really.

748
01:20:23,248 --> 01:20:25,916
Oh, I thank you, Betty...

749
01:20:26,001 --> 01:20:28,628
and I really mean that sincerely.

750
01:20:28,712 --> 01:20:31,631
I mean, it was extraordinary.

751
01:20:32,883 --> 01:20:34,800
You've done your aunt proud today.

752
01:20:34,885 --> 01:20:38,804
I am going to tell her that
first chance I get.

753
01:20:38,889 --> 01:20:41,307
Now, you and I ...

754
01:20:41,391 --> 01:20:43,309
are going to speak again very soon.

755
01:20:43,393 --> 01:20:45,686
Thank you, Mr. Brown.

756
01:20:45,771 --> 01:20:47,688
Thank you, Wally.

757
01:20:47,773 --> 01:20:51,108
I'm sure you all have a lot to talk about.
We'll walk Betty out.

758
01:20:51,193 --> 01:20:55,112
Oh, well, yes, indeed.
And it was our pleasure, Linney.

759
01:20:55,197 --> 01:20:57,698
Now, don't you be a stranger around here.

760
01:20:57,783 --> 01:21:00,743
- We'd love to have you here.
- Come on, Betty.

761
01:21:00,827 --> 01:21:02,745
Thank you again, Mr. Brown.

762
01:21:02,829 --> 01:21:07,833
And it was nice meeting all of you.
Bye.

763
01:21:09,586 --> 01:21:11,170
Bye.

764
01:21:13,590 --> 01:21:16,509
- Wow!
- She's a slam dunk.

765
01:21:16,593 --> 01:21:18,511
Where the hell did you find her?

766
01:21:18,595 --> 01:21:20,763
God, that was awful.

767
01:21:22,265 --> 01:21:24,850
Not you, Betty.
You were stellar. And I mean that.

768
01:21:24,935 --> 01:21:26,644
But poor Wally.

769
01:21:26,728 --> 01:21:28,938
- He'll never get that picture made.
- No.

770
01:21:29,022 --> 01:21:31,315
Wally's days were up 20 years ago.

771
01:21:31,400 --> 01:21:34,527
You know Woody Katz
is only doing it for a favor.

772
01:21:34,611 --> 01:21:36,696
And the cast, I hear, so far is terrible.

773
01:21:36,780 --> 01:21:38,864
Oh, God, terrible.

774
01:21:38,949 --> 01:21:41,200
That poor old fool Wally.

775
01:21:41,284 --> 01:21:45,204
He was very nice,
and he seemed so sweet.

776
01:21:45,288 --> 01:21:48,249
And Wally – Mr. Brown –
is a very close friend of my aunt's, and –

777
01:21:48,333 --> 01:21:51,293
Settle down, Betty.
Don't get me wrong. I love Wally.

778
01:21:51,378 --> 01:21:55,005
I ought to.
